    "title": "本年第三季度较第二季度环比变动说明：",
    "page_range": "33",
    "summary": "This section explains the quarter-over-quarter (Q2 to Q3) performance changes, centered on a line chart (Figure) tracking regional game server metrics from mid-July to late December. It defines visual legend mappings (cyan-green area for aggregated totals; blue, yellow, and orange lines for individual servers) and covers four entities: “三服合计” (combined three servers), “国服（仅App Store）” (China App Store), “繁中服” (Traditional Chinese), and “日服” (Japanese). Key metrics highlight temporal extremes, with the combined total peaking at ~1,600 and troughing at ~200, while regional servers range from ~800 to ~50 at peaks and ~100 to ~50 at lows. The analysis claims a consistent downward trajectory across all categories following a synchronous mid-July surge, noting significantly higher volatility in the Traditional Chinese server compared to the stable China and Japan servers, with all individual trends closely aligning with the combined total. Evidence is derived from observational chart data independently researched and visualized by 点点数据 (DianDian Data). No tables or procedures are included."
