    "page_range": "1",
    "summary": "This section outlines the core design framework and post-launch operational strategy of 《杖剑传说》, enabling retrieval of answers to the following:\n- **Topics & Definitions:** The “放置为表、MMO为里” (idle surface, MMO core) design philosophy; semi-real-time command queue combat; BD (build) construction via 8-slot active/passive skill and equipment stat synergy.\n- **Procedures & Mechanics:** Low-barrier daily idle progression and light exploration loops; pre-matching skill combinations; transition to team-dependent high-yield dungeon challenges; guild system participation.\n- **Claims & Metrics:** The hybrid design lowers daily participation thresholds while ensuring long-term strategic depth; social dynamics (“大佬带本” culture, guilds) and frequent IP partnerships (~every 2 months) are primary drivers for player retention and revenue; public beta duration exceeds half a year.\n- **Entities & Dates:** Specific post-launch IP collaborations and their rollout timelines relative to launch: 蔬菜精灵 (synchronous with public beta), 为美好的世界献上祝福 (2 months post-launch), 洛天依×言和 (4 months post-launch), 罗小黑战记2 (6 months post-launch).\n- **Figures & Evidence Types:** A chronological timeline chart tracking collab frequency, sourced from 点点数据 (Diandian Data) research. Strategic claims are supported by gameplay system analysis and arguments regarding the high compatibility of the game’s pure 2D art style with core ACG IP fan conversion."
